+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013syEpkcZ5EZZMk5B7bZ865","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have a complete picture of the project structure. Here's my comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Structure Summary\n\n### Overview\nThis is a **Circuit Debugger** project - a TypeScript-based reasoning benchmark for simulating logic gate circuits and detecting swapped wires in binary adder circuits.\n\n### File Structure\n\n**Root Directory Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - NPM package configuration\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript compiler configuration\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Main test runner configuration\n- `/workspace/validation-vitest.config.ts` - Validation test configuration\n- `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs` - ESLint configuration\n- `/workspace/TASK.md` - Project specification and requirements\n- `/workspace/.gitignore` - Git ignore rules\n- `/workspace/src/` - Source code directory (currently empty except for `.gitkeep`)\n\n### Package Configuration\n\n**package.json Details:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-circuit-debugger\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Circuit debugger reasoning benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Info:**\n- ES Module project (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- TypeScript 5.4\n- Vitest 2.0 for testing\n- ESLint with TypeScript support\n\n### TypeScript Configuration\n\n**tsconfig.json Details:**\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution