(x03, y03) -> z03` (was a03)\n- ... (bit 4 normal)\n- `XOR(t05, c04) -> b05` (was z05)\n- `AND(t05, c04) -> z05` (was b05)  \n- ...\n- `XOR(x07, y07) -> a07` (was t07)\n- `AND(x07, y07) -> t07` (was a07)\n\nFor R10, carryWires includes OR gates outputs that aren't swapped:\n- c01 (OR, bit 1), c02 (OR, bit 2), c03 (OR, bit 3), etc.\n- c00 is an OR gate? No, c00 is the output of the XOR in the swapped circuit. Original c00 was AND output, now z00.\n\nHmm wait: in the original 8-bit adder, there IS no OR gate for bit 0. There's just AND(x00,y00)->c00. After swap, AND(x00,y00)->z00.\n\nSo for the carry chain check with c06 (OR gate, bit 6):\n- Bit 6: getOrGateBit finds the generate AND for bit 6. carry = c06. nextBit = 7.\n- The XOR consumer of c06 should be the second-stage XOR for bit 7.\n- After the t07<->a07 swap: `XOR(x07, y07) -> a07` and `AND(x07, y07) -> t07`.\n- The second-stage XOR for bit 7 is `XOR(t07, c06) -> z07`.\n- t07 is now produced by AND(x07, y07), not XOR(x07, y07).\n- consumers[c06] includes {XOR, t07, c06, z07} and {AND, t07, c06, b07}.\n- The XOR consumer: other input is t07. gateByOutput[t07] = AND(x07, y07) → op is AND, not XOR.\n- So the check \"otherProducer.op === 'XOR'\" fails, and it falls to the else branch which adds c06.\n\nBut c06 ISN'T swapped! The problem is that t07 (the partial sum for bit 7) has been swapped to be produced by AND instead of XOR. My carry check incorrectly flags c06 because the partial sum it pairs with is wrong.\n\nThe fix: when the other input's producer is wrong (not XOR(xN,yN)), I should flag the **other input** as potentially swapped, not the carry wire. Or better yet, I should not flag the carry if the other input is already identified as a swap.\n\nLet me refine R10:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1557,"cache_read_input_tokens":97101,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1557},"output_tokens":1,"service_