pped.has(t07) = true. For nextBitOutputs {t03, z03}: swapped.has(t03)? No. swapped.has(z03)? Yes (R5 flagged it). So carryAtCorrectBit = true.\n\nThe last resort check incorrectly concludes the carry is fine because z03 is in both nextBitOutputs and swapped. But the reason z03 is swapped has nothing to do with c06.\n\nThe \"last resort\" check is fundamentally flawed. The co-occurrence of `otherInput in swapped` and `some nextBitOutput in swapped` doesn't imply they are swap partners.\n\nLet me remove the last resort check entirely and instead handle this more carefully:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1573,"cache_read_input_tokens":140440,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1573},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c9cc341-f7e8-430e-9a27-173fe58a503e","uuid":"61a29ecb-f9c0-49b3-8942-2c3e504e5639"}
